{
  "text": "Ventricular tachycardias (VTs) increase mortality in patients with a structure heart disease. [CITATION_1] To manage the VTs in this population, there are three feasible options: antiarrhythmic drugs (AADs), implantable cardioverter-defibrillator (ICD), and catheter ablation (CA).",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "28281338"
